How can I modify this [Go code] function to add greetings based on the day of the week? Specifically, I want to return "Happy weekend!" on Saturdays and Sundays, and "Hope you have a great start to your week!" on Mondays. If someone greets me with "Good morning!" on a Monday, what would be the appropriate response using this updated function? 
[Go code] 
```go
func greetingByTimeOfDay() string {
    today := time.Now()
    weekday := today.Weekday()
    hour := today.Hour()
    if weekday == time.Saturday || weekday == time.Sunday {
        return "Happy weekend!"
    } else if weekday == time.Monday {
        return "Hope you have a great start to your week!"
    } else if hour >= 5 && hour < 12 {
        return "Good morning!"
    } else if hour >= 12 && hour < 18 {
        return "Good afternoon!"
    } else if hour >= 18 && hour < 21 {
        return "Good evening!"
    } else if (hour >= 21 && today.Minute() >= 30) || (hour < 5) {
        return "Good night!"
    }
    return ""
}
```

To modify the given Go function to add greetings based on the day of the week, we can adjust the logic inside the function. Here's how you can modify it:

1. Check if the day is Saturday or Sunday to return "Happy weekend!".
2. On Monday, check if the time of the day is morning and return "Hope you have a great start to your week!" when greeted with "Good morning!".
3. Adjust other greetings based on the time of the day.

Here's the updated Go code:

```go
package main

import (
    "fmt"
    "time"
)

func greetingByTimeOfDay(greeting string) string {
    today := time.Now()
    weekday := today.Weekday()
    hour := today.Hour()

    if weekday == time.Saturday || weekday == time.Sunday {
        return "Happy weekend!"
    } else if weekday == time.Monday {
        if greeting == "Good morning!" {
            return "Hope you have a great start to your week!"
        }
        return "Hope you have a great start to your week!"
    } else if hour >= 5 && hour < 12 {
        return "Good morning!"
    } else if hour >= 12 && hour < 18 {
        return "Good afternoon!"
    } else if hour >= 18 && hour < 21 {
        return "Good evening!"
    } else if (hour >= 21 && today.Minute() >= 30) || (hour < 5) {
        return "Good night!"
    }
    return ""
}

func main() {
    fmt.Println(greetingByTimeOfDay("Good morning!"))
}
```

### Explanation:
- The function `greetingByTimeOfDay` now takes an argument `greeting` that represents the greeting message received.
- On Mondays, if the received `greeting` is "Good morning!", it returns a specific message "Hope you have a great start to your week!".
- For Saturdays and Sundays, it returns "Happy weekend!" regardless of the time of the day.
- For other days, it checks the time to provide the appropriate greeting.

When someone greets you with "Good morning!" on a Monday, the function will return "Hope you have a great start to your week!".
